iao_definition: ['A pyridinemonocarboxylic acid that is pyridine-2-carboxylic acid which is substituted by a chloro group at positions 3,5 and 6, and by an amino group at position 4. It is a systemic herbicide used to control deeply rooted herbaceous weeds and woody plants in rights-of-way, forestry, range lands, pastures, and small grain crops.']
oio_related_synonym: ['3,5,6-trichloro-4-amino-2-pyridinecarboxylic acid', '3,5,6-trichloro-4-aminopicolinic acid', '4-amino-3,5,6-trichloro-2-picolinic acid', '4-amino-3,5,6-trichloro-2-pyridinecarboxylic acid', '4-amino-3,5,6-trichloropicolinic acid', 'Access', 'Amdon', 'Borolin', 'Grazon', 'K-Pin', 'Pathway', 'picloram acid', 'piclorame', 'Tordon']
label: ['picloram']

iao_definition: ['A pyridinemonocarboxylic acid in which the carboxy group is located at position 2. It is an intermediate in the metabolism of tryptophan.']
oio_related_synonym: ['2-carboxypyridine', '2-Picolinic acid', '2-Pyridinecarboxylic acid', 'alpha-picolinic acid', 'alpha-pyridinecarboxylic acid', 'o-pyridinecarboxylic acid', 'PYRIDINE-2-CARBOXYLIC ACID']
label: ['picolinic acid']

iao_definition: ['*Lithospermum arvense*, the field gromwell, corn gromwell, or bastard alkanet, is a flowering plant of the family *Boraginaceae*. It is also known as *Buglossoides arvensis*. The European Union has granted the refined oil of the seed of *Buglossoides arvensis* novel food status and some farmers are growing it. [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lithospermum_arvense]']
label: ['Buglossoides arvensis']
oio_narrow_synonym: ['Buglossoides arvensis (L.) I. M. Johnst.', 'Buglossoides arvensis (L.) I.M. Johnst.', 'Lithospermum arvense L.']

iao_definition: ['Intended use of the molecular entity or part thereof by humans.']
label: ['application']

iao_definition: ['A matured ovule containing an embryo and food supply and covered by a seed coat.']
label: ['seed']

iao_definition: ['When two or more amino acids combine to form a peptide, the elements of water are removed, and what remains of each amino acid is called an amino-acid residue.']
label: ['amino-acid residue']

iao_definition: ['A monocarboxylic acid in which the carboxy group is attached to a pyridine (or substituted pyridine) ring.']
label: ['pyridinemonocarboxylic acid']

iao_definition: ['Any organochlorine compound that has been used as a pesticide.']
label: ['organochlorine pesticide']

iao_definition: ['Compounds containing a pyridine nucleus substituted with one or more chlorine atoms.']
label: ['chloropyridine']

iao_definition: ['"A feeding behavior associated with the intake of food." [NBO:GVG]']
label: ['food consumption']

iao_definition: ['Slow, creeping onset, slow progress and long continuance of disease manifestations.']
label: ['Chronic']
rdf_comment: ['According to the U.S. National Center for Health Statistics, a chronic condition is one lasting 3 months or more.']
